casebody.data:
Will Stubblefield v. The State. No. 8942. Delivered April 22, 1925.

The opinion states the case.

No brief filed by appellant. Tom Garrard, State’s Attorney, and Grover G. Morris, Assistant State’s Attorney, for the State. MORROW, Presiding Judge.

The offense is the unlawful manufacture of intoxicating liquor; punishment fixed at confinement in the penitentiary for one year.

The witnesses for the State gave direct testimony showing the commission of the offense. The testimony is uncontroverted. The indictment is regular. No complaint is made of the charge of the court or of the rulings upon the conduct of the trial.

The judgment is affirmed.

Affirmed.
